items.name: Tessia Eralith (The Beginning After The End - TBATE) LoRA
items.description:
Tessia Eralith from the web novel/manga The Beginning After the End. Works well on 0.6-1.0. Training done on NAI.

Trigger:

  • "tessia" for the main look without the outfits.

  • "tesBattle, armor" for the armor outfit.

  • "tesXyrus, school uniform" for her Academy outfit.

  • Use only one outfit at a time else the outfits will blend together.

Recommended:

  • For Armored outfit can help adding "black bodysuit, armor, single shoulder pad, breast plate, arm guards, hip armor" but is not needed much.

  • For Academy outfit adding "white capelet, capelet, school uniform, blue skirt, blue vest, white jacket, knee boots, long sleeves" can help depending on what is having trouble appearing but it is not super needed.

This LoRA I used as practice to train in several outfits and had success but they are sometimes missing a bit or two as the data was lacking and she has a very complicated outfit but adding some of the above tags can help fix it.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated. Hope you enjoy the LoRA.

items.name: Chougei (Kancolle)
items.description:
An experimental character LoRA of Chougei from Kantai Collection.

Info

Training with 85 images
Followed the manual form [ [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free ],
You can access to this guide in Suggested Resources section.

Recommended set up

Sampler: Euler a, DPM family series
Sampling steps: 20 or 25+
CFG Scale: 7
CLIP Skip: 2
*Do not use [restore face] on anime character!*

LoRA Weighting: [1 - 0.7], (1 - 0.6)

Baking Step:
0. Drafting (512 x 512 res to find your desired sketch)
1. Hires fix (txt2img: 768 x 768, 768 x 512, 512 x 768, or above res)
2. inpaint (img2img: refine some unwanted effect, [Euler a] with 50+ step)
3. Upscaling (img2img: res*2 with [ControlNet Tile] & Ultimate SD upscale)

Upscaler for [Step 1 - 3]: [R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, 4x-AnimeSharp, 4x-UltraSharp]
I always skip Step 0, 2 :P

Basic prompts

ChougeiKC, blue serafuku, blue sailor collar, white neckerchief, blue pleated skirt, shawl, bandana, white waist apron, black thighhighs

Some additional tags that you may use for reference

-headgear, hair ornament, hairclip
-holding cup, drinking glass, drinking straw
-swimsuit, orange bikini, front-tie top, (barefoot / sandals, flip-flops), visor cap, white jacket, open jacket, hair flower, cleavage, navel

items.name: _dabdabil artstyle [LyCORIS]
items.description:
Your feedback is greatly appreciated. Please post your results and reviews, so that I could see what to change or alter in my subsequent LoRAs and revisions.

This LoRA is based on the works of _dabdabil (aka Dabi_Bill). If you enjoy this model, you can go ahead and give him a sub on Twitter and/or Instagram.

Dataset:

Manually sorted and cropped 352 images, 896x896 resolution. Trained on low speed with 1 repeat for 18 epochs on "AnyLoRA" checkpoint.

Testing:

Overall testing took upwards of 6+ hours. I took great care to test for overtraining and settled on epoch 16. Tested both anime 2D and 2.5D checkpoints. Tested with other LoRAs, embeddings, etc.

Strenghts:

  • Aimed at generating teens/young adults.

  • Facial expressions are both diverse and easy to prompt (very close to original ones).

  • Exceptional at generating portraits, bodyshots. Easily handles both SFW and NFSW.

  • Compatible with almost any other LoRA, negative embedding, etc.

  • Can be used to remove the "porcelain doll face" found in some 2.5D models (e.g. REV Animated).

Weak points:

  • The style itself is very sketch-ish/simplistic. This means that it will simplify the output. If you are using a very low detail Anime model (Grapefruit, Orange Mix, etc.), you may (in certain situations) experience lack of detail. This can be aided by either lowering the strenght from 1 to 0.8, using BREAK command in the middle of the prompt, or by using the "Add detail" LoRA.

  • When used with higher resolutions it may occasionally (5-10% of the time) generate speech bubbles or comic strips. This is caused by the dataset and may be improved in subsequent versions.

items.description:
The man, the myth, the legend himself...

Be nice. Have Fun!

Nicolas Kim Coppola (born January 7, 1964),[1][2] known by his stage name Nicolas Cage, is an American actor and film producer. Born into the Coppola family, he is the recipient of various accolades, including an Academy Award, a Screen Actors Guild Award, and a Golden Globe Award.

Cage first gained attention for his romantic roles in Valley Girl (1983), Peggy Sue Got Married (1986) and Moonstruck (1987), and gained praise for playing an ex-convict in the black comedy Raising Arizona (1987). For starring as an alcoholic in Leaving Las Vegas (1995), he won the Academy Award for Best Actor. He received another Academy Award nomination for his performance as twins Charlie and Donald Kaufman in Adaptation (2002).

Cage established himself in mainstream action films, such as The Rock (1996), Con Air (1997), Face/Off (1997), Gone in 60 Seconds (2000), the National Treasure film series (2004‚Äì2007), the Ghost Rider film series (2007‚Äì2011), and Kick-Ass (2010). He also took on dramatic roles in City of Angels (1998), Bringing Out the Dead (1999), and The Family Man (2000). He has voiced characters in The Croods franchise (2013‚Äìpresent) and in Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse (2018). He earned renewed critical recognition for his starring roles in Mandy (2018), Pig (2021), and The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent (2022).[3][4]

Cage owns the production company Saturn Films and has produced films such as Shadow of the Vampire (2000) and The Life of David Gale (2003), and has directed Sonny (2002). He was ranked No. 40 in Empire magazine's The Top 100 Movie Stars of All Time list in 2007 and was placed No. 37 in Premiere's 100 Most Powerful People in Hollywood in 2008.

items.name: Pansy
items.description:
What is Pansy?

Pansy is a model primarily used for creating photorealistic or realistic images. It is great in generating characters, portraits, sceneries and more. Just like my other models, this has its own unique aesthetics. Regarding text prompts, just be versatile and let your imagination flow. And, just like most models it also has few issues with the hands, which can be easily mitigated with this model's inpainting (download separately) or some embeddings. (I still have other models, for some specific arts, yet to be released. Your support will go a long way, and a cup of coffee will keep me awake for many nights. Thank you in advance!)

This version of Pansy does not include a VAE because the goal is for art versatility, wherein, you can use any VAE you like to produce unique aesthetics. Below are the recommended VAEs that you can use with this model to tweak a unique output.

Popular Variable Auto Encoder (VAE)

kl-f8-anime2 VAE (for anime)

anything VAE aka orangemix VAE (for anime)

blessed VAE (for anime)

vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realism)

Sample images above were created with simple text prompts around default settings. More detailed prompts will produce much better results. As for text prompts, just let your imagination flow. One thing to take note, adding keywords like realistic, realism, photorealism, photorealistic, hyperrealism, hyper realistic etc. will make the image more real, and not including any word with real on them will make it look anime-ish.

Settings:

Sampling Method: Euler (realistic) or Euler A (anime)

Sampling Steps: 20 to 30

Resolution: 512x512, 512x768, 768x512

CFG Scale: 4 to 7

Popular Embeddings Used:

Easy Negative

Deep Negative

Bad artist Negative embedding

veryBadImageNegative

bad_prompt Negative Embedding

negative_hand Negative Embedding

EnvyBetterHands LoCon

Detail Tweaker LoRA

SXZ Vivid Darkness

Theovercomer8's Contrast Fix

Limitations:

Do use this model within the boundaries of legalities; do not use it to harm people and entities, or any illegal matters. Using this model means that you alone are responsible for any forms of consequences good or bad, and the author has no liabilities. We all know that AI models can produce both safe and unsafe images for work, so be very responsible.¬† For all other matters do read the CreativeML-OpenRail-M license Other than that, enjoy using this model and I hope this will help you in your endeavors as an artist.

Support:

First of all, thank you for patronizing this model; it means my efforts didn't go to waste. My goal is to produce more free tools not just for myself and my work, but for others too. Your generosity will go more than a mile. Also, as an artist, writer, programmer, and overall freelancer, I accept commission job. Thank you so much for your support!

items.description:
If you enjoyed this model, why don't you check out my other works? I put a lot of effort into correctly recreating artist styles and making the occasional character LoRA.üòä

This model was trained using the collab/guide by holostrawberry [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free - colabs | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

About the artist:

This artist creates very nsfw content. Fuya has a penchant for very large breasts and a generally thicc body type. The model was almost exclusively trained on newer images with minimal SFW content included and therefore excells at prompts along those lines in particular.

Twitter: FUYAüîûPATREON (@fuyafuyu) / Twitter

Gumroad: Fuya (gumroad.com)

Pixiv: FUYA - pixiv

Weights & Prompts

The only necessary prompt is

Fuya

Note that any other checkpoint affects the effectiveness of this model. The same goes for most character LoRA that weren't trained well enough.

NAI:

This should be your goto version with most checkpoints.

Use a weight of 1.0, adjust to taste.

AOM3:

Use a weight of 1.0, adjust to taste. As usual I have included an XYZ plot for reference.

Lightweight character models can be used at the same or higher weight (I tried up to 1.3) but, in my experience, are a bit more likely to have deformed hands.

For inspiration check the examples. I recommend heavily experimenting with the steps as well. Sometimes a 12 step image is just what you want, sometimes it takes 30 to get the necessary detail.

(Backgrounds and objects in general are barely affected in this model.)

Please leave a review if you enjoyed this model or have problems with it. I'd also be interested in how the model behaves with other base checkpoints, so why don't you give it a try and throw some images down below! üëá

items.name: SeekGold
items.description:
Hi again and welcome to SeekGold.

SeekGold is part of the "Seek" series (you probably already saw my SeekWest) where I focus more doing a world-embedding instead of a characters or landscapes only. SeekGold will create gold, metal gold, abstract dripping landscapes, characters, etc.

This is also my first public Lycoris (LoCon in this case).

For curious people, I have been messing for couple months training LoCons and LoHa's privately and now it's time to upload (and retraining) them since I polished my training, dataset, etc. (meanwhile I get ready for SDXL).

Token is LQDGOD

How does this works?
*************************

  • FIRST OF ALL: Make sure you have everything ready to use LyCoris on your WebUI. Install this extension on your WebUI (Recommended if you have an older repo).

  • I also recommendto use this negative embedding:
    https://civitai.com/models/7808/easynegative

  • Or this combination words:
    "glass, pedestal, socle, basement, camera, subsurface, underwater, hypermaximalist, diamond, (flowers), water, (leaves) (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), border, frame, poorly drawn, childish,((dof)),bad hands, ugly hands, unnatural hands"

    Back to the embedding:

- It works on every model I have tested and at some high degree of flexibility. I'd recommend RevAnimated but you can go Colorful, Faetastic, Dreamshaper, AnyLora, etc. I'd recommend Clip Skip 2 but with 1 also works (I think a bit worse).

- You can go from 0.6-1 (with the new LyCoris extension).

- You can go from 0.9-1.3 (With the old one, the one I used to create the outputs)
(read the comments for this, please).

- Prompt like normal but add "in the style of LQDGOD", "LQDGOD concept", etc.

- There are subtokens like dripping and gold which drags more to the style but most of the time you won't need them since token is very very powerful.

- If you feel that the style is killing the concept (which is probable in the new LyCoris extension) consider to go under 0.9 till 0.6.

- You can prompt with the LoCon without the token using subtokens and words dragging to the style.

This model is good for
************************

- Characters wearing gold objects, armors, suits. and statuesque alike.
- Characters mixed with gold element and "symbio"
- Abstract gold landscapes and gold type structures or vehicles.
- Dripping materials


This model is NOT designed for:
**************************************

- It wasn't test on Realistic models so I can't say it will work as in the others.

IMPORTANT!

I wrote an article here and it's like my finetunning diary for the ones interested with releases upcoming, trainings done, exclusive patreon models previews, personal thoughts, etc. So if you want to see what I'm planning or what I'm into, feel free to take a look.

Thanks as always for all the support and please keep supporting me and my pal so we can create more quality content in our Patreon for you all.


Feel free to throw feedbacks, reviews (thanks guys!), critics and so on. I always read them and make all on my hand to make quality things.

David.

items.name: CloneCleaner wildcards - increase character consistency
items.description:
https://github.com/artyfacialintelagent/CloneCleaner
in wildcard form. This greatly helps with identity consistency. The extension is good but I needed to use it through the api.

I generated 1GB of names, deduped, and selected 200,000 at random. There is a 4.2 million entry one as well (personfull). The personfull is slower to load and is not cached by a111.

Full version available with better animations on my personal site

https://ntcai.xyz/conceptmod/clone_cleaner/

Use with __person__ or __personfull__

Example:
> Jasmine from USA, medium (chin-length:1.2) straight [mahogany:.2] hair

Usage:

Extract the txt and move it to <a111>/extensions/stable-diffusion-webui-wildcards/wildcards

Do not drag and drop to the ui like other instructions say. A111 freezes.

Animations made with https://github.com/ntc-ai/conceptmod . They use mostly released conceptmod loras.

Note:

This does not include male names. This is due to the original CloneCleaner script not including male names.

items.name: Kelly LeBrock (80s)
items.description:
Kelly LeBrock is an American actress and model, known mainly for her roles in 80s movies such as The Woman in Red or Weird Science.

200-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (klebr0ck:0.99), a woman as a movie star, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"
